GloSSH is a permissively-licensed secure-transport stack for ESP-IDF,
created to replace copyleft/commercial dependencies (wolfSSH / wolfSSL).
It bundles the following third-party software, each under its own
permissive or public-domain terms. None of these are copyleft.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dropbear SSH  (components/dropbear/dropbear, v2020.81)
  Copyright (c) 2002-2020 Matt Johnston, and others.
  MIT-style license. See components/dropbear/dropbear/LICENSE.

  Dropbear bundles, under its own tree:
    * LibTomCrypt  (components/dropbear/dropbear/libtomcrypt)
        Public domain (Tom St Denis / The LibTom Projects).
    * LibTomMath   (components/dropbear/dropbear/libtommath)
        Public domain (Tom St Denis / The LibTom Projects).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
TinySSH  (components/tinyssh/tinyssh)
  Copyright (c) Jan Mojzis.
  Public domain (CC0 1.0 fallback). See components/tinyssh/tinyssh/LICENCE.
  Includes reference public-domain cryptography (NaCl/ref10 lineage).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The upstream license texts are retained verbatim within each vendored
source tree. THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md indexes them.
